                <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-800">Question 2 (3 marks)</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2 font-medium">
                  Distinguish between open loop and closed loop control systems.
                </p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mb-4">
                <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4">
                  <div class="space-y-2">
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                    <div class="border-b border-gray-300 h-6"></div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <details class="mt-6">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-green-50 p-3 rounded text-green-800 font-medium hover:bg-green-100">
                  ðŸ“‹ View Marking Criteria & Sample Answer
                </summary>
                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
                  <div class="mb-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Marking Criteria:</h4>
                    <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
                      <li><strong>3 marks:</strong> Clearly distinguishes between open and closed loop systems with specific contrasting features (e.g., feedback presence vs absence)</li>
                      <li><strong>2 marks:</strong> Identifies key differences between both systems but lacks clear distinction or specific contrasting examples</li>
                      <li><strong>1 mark:</strong> Describes one system correctly but fails to distinguish from the other OR provides vague differences</li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>Open loop systems operate without feedback and cannot adjust their output based on results, whereas closed loop systems use sensor feedback to monitor their output and make automatic adjustments. For example, a toaster (open loop) runs for a set time regardless of how brown the bread is, while a thermostat (closed loop) continuously monitors temperature and adjusts heating to maintain the desired temperature.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>
