                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p><strong>Cause-and-effect structure:</strong></p>
                      <p>The temperature sensor continuously monitors room temperature and sends this data to the processor (cause), which compares the current temperature to the desired setting (effect). When the temperature drops below the set point (cause), the processor signals the heating actuator to turn on the furnace (effect). Once the sensor detects that the desired temperature is reached (cause), the processor turns off the heating actuator, creating a continuous feedback loop that maintains comfortable temperature automatically (effect).</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </details>
