                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>Closed loop systems use sensor feedback to ensure precise positioning and movement of robotic arms, which is essential for accurate assembly and welding operations. They can adapt to variations in part dimensions or positioning that commonly occur in manufacturing, whereas open loop systems would continue with predetermined movements regardless of actual conditions. The continuous monitoring and adjustment capability of closed loop systems ensures consistent quality and reduces waste from defective products.</p>
