                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Sample Answer:</h4>
                    <div class="text-sm bg-white p-3 rounded border">
                      <p>More degrees of freedom allow robotic arms to position and orient their end-effector (tool) with greater flexibility (cause), enabling them to reach complex angles and positions that would be impossible with fewer DOF (effect). For example, a 6-DOF robot can position its welding tool at any location (X,Y,Z coordinates) and orient it at any angle (roll, pitch, yaw) (cause), allowing it to weld complex geometries like car body panels from multiple angles (effect). However, additional degrees of freedom increase system complexity and cost, so the optimal number depends on the specific application requirements.</p>
                    </div>
